{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Job|37","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","chapter":37,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":1,"text":"My heart pounds at this and leaps from my chest.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":2,"text":"Just listen to his thunderous voice and the rumbling that comes from his mouth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":3,"text":"He lets it loose beneath the entire sky; his lightning to the ends of the earth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":4,"text":"Then there comes a roaring sound; God thunders with his majestic voice. He does not restrain the lightning when his rumbling voice is heard.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":5,"text":"God thunders wondrously with his voice; he does great things that we cannot comprehend.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":6,"text":"For he says to the snow, “Fall to the earth,” and the torrential rains, his mighty torrential rains,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":7,"text":"serve as his sign to all mankind, so that all men may know his work.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":8,"text":"The wild animals enter their lairs and stay in their dens.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":9,"text":"The windstorm comes from its chamber, and the cold from the driving north winds.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":10,"text":"Ice is formed by the breath of God, and watery expanses are frozen.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":11,"text":"He saturates clouds with moisture; he scatters his lightning through them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":12,"text":"They swirl about, turning round and round at his direction, accomplishing everything he commands them over the surface of the inhabited world.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":13,"text":"He causes this to happen for punishment, for his land, or for his faithful love.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":14,"text":"Listen to this, Job. Stop and consider God’s wonders.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":15,"text":"Do you know how God directs his clouds or makes their lightning flash?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":16,"text":"Do you understand how the clouds float, those wonderful works of him who has perfect knowledge?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":17,"text":"You whose clothes get hot when the south wind brings calm to the land,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":18,"text":"can you help God spread out the skies as hard as a cast metal mirror?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":19,"text":"Teach us what we should say to him; we cannot prepare our case because of our darkness.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":20,"text":"Should he be told that I want to speak? Can a man speak when he is confused?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":21,"text":"Now no one can even look at the sun after a wind has swept through and cleared the sky.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":22,"text":"Out of the north he comes, shrouded in a golden glow; awesome majesty surrounds him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:37:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":37,"verse":23,"text":"Th